 # Changelog
 
+## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S6-P03-T074 (Shadow source-silence prediction; SHADOW)
+
+- Seventy-fourth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (opens S6-P03). Predicts whether an official source's current quiet is abnormal (it should have published by now) or normal (within its cadence), and distinguishes abnormal source silence from a collection failure (our fetcher broke). release_mode SHADOW; predictions are computed in the dev/shadow environment only, the production worker/cron/data untouched, 0 cloud cost, DIR-007 unaffected, and the realtime build is unchanged. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/silence_predictor.py: cadence (median inter-publication interval + MAD), simple_cycle_overdue (the baseline: overdue if the gap exceeds the median interval), classify (the model: a fetch error -> collection_failure; otherwise abnormal only if the gap exceeds median + k*MAD, a robust allowance for the source's own variability; returns normal/abnormal_silence/collection_failure), and evaluate (scores the model AND the baseline on the same labeled truth: accuracy, false-alarm rate, human value). Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S6-P03-T074/: silence_predictor_report.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S6-P03-T074/test-results/silence_predictor_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): the model beats the simple publication-cycle baseline (accuracy 1.0 vs 0.667, false-alarm rate 0.0 vs 0.5, human value 4 vs 3) because its robust threshold does not false-alarm on a naturally-variable source and its fetch-error signal distinguishes a collection failure the baseline calls source silence; false alarms and human value are quantified numbers from the outcomes; and the model classifies a fetch failure as collection_failure while the cadence-only baseline cannot, and still catches a genuinely-abnormal silence on a variable source (it is not over-conservative). Realtime not regressed (no production deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0, recurring cloud 0 (SHADOW dev env). Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S6-P02-T073 (calibration + skill scores + append-only Forecast Ledger; NOT_DEPLOYED)
 
 - Seventy-third task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S6-P02). Preserves successes AND failures over the long run -- never just the pretty cases: a reliability diagram (calibration), Brier skill score / logloss, and an append-only, tamper-evident Forecast Ledger. Any user-visible probability must have historical calibration (its probability bin has data) and a failure record can never be deleted. release_mode NOT_DEPLOYED; a read-only library of metrics over the T072 backtest outputs (no new predictive model, operational MODEL_SPEC/formula_registry untouched), the production worker/cron/data untouched. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/forecast_ledger.py: calibration (10-bin reliability diagram: per-bin predicted mean vs observed frequency vs count), has_calibration / calibration_of (a user-visible probability is calibration-backed only when its bin has history; a non-numeric probability is not, no crash), brier_skill_score (1 - Brier(model)/Brier(reference); negative skill reported honestly), logloss, and an append-only Ledger (append records both successes and failures with a per-record hash chained from the previous, delete() raises AppendOnlyError, verify_integrity() detects any deletion/mutation of a record). Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S6-P02-T073/: forecast_ledger_report.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S6-P02-T073/test-results/forecast_ledger_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): the reliability diagram has four populated bins whose predicted mean equals the observed frequency (0.2/0.5/0.8/0.9), a user-visible probability in a covered bin is calibration-backed while an uncovered probability (0.35) and a non-numeric one are not; a failure record is preserved, delete() raises for both a failure and a success, and directly popping or mutating a failure (bypassing delete) breaks verify_integrity; and skill is honest (BSS 0.636 for a model that beats the reference, 0 for an equal model, -0.364 for a worse one). Realtime not regressed (no deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
